

### Caesar Salad
### NYTimes, p. 175 [1947]

* 1 clove garlic, peeled
* 1 head romaine
* 2 oz Parmesan
* 1/4 tsp Colman's mustard
* 3 Tbsp olive oil
* 1 Tbsp lemon juice
* 1 egg (room temperature)

* Rub inside of wood salad bowl with garlic clove
* add romaine, salt, pepper, parmesan, mustard, oil, lemon juice

* coddle egg
** bring small saucepan to boil
** lower the egg into the water and simmer for 2 exactly minutes

* remove water, break into salad
* toss moderately
* add croutons immediately before serving


### Lisa's Favorite Caesar Sald
### Perini p.65

Dressing:
* 6 t olive oil
* 6 cloves garlic, chopped
* 1 t dry mustard
* 1 t pepper
* 1 t salt
* 3 t capers with juice
* 3 anchovies
* 2 T tarragon vinegar
* 2 T lemon juice

Salad:
* 1 head romaine
* 1/3 C grated parmesan
* 2 C sourdough croutons

Combine dressing ingredients; mix thoroughly
Toss with chilled romaine lettuce and sprinkle with parmesan, sourdough



### Red Chile Caesar Salad with Grilled Radicchio and Romaine
### Fearing p. 97

* 1 head radicchio, cut in half lengthwise
* 2 Tbsp olive oil
* 2 large heads romaine, trimmed, outer leaves removed, cut into 1-inch pieces
* 3/4 cup smoked chile aioli (p.35)
* 1/2 cup crumbled san pedro cheese
* 1/2 cup diced tomatoes
* 1/2 cup julienned fresh hearts of palm

* lightly coat radicchio with salt, pepper, olive oil
* place radicchio, cut side down, on the hot grill; 2 minutes, 2 sides
* slice radicchio into thin shreds; transfer to plate and refrigerate
* toss romaine in large bowl with a little salt
* add radicchio and half the cheese; toss again
* 




